<br>
Hands down one of the best additions to the game in recent history. It is soooo nice having a place to bind yer soul without chasing down another player ta do it, especially considering low server population and langauge issues. Kudos to Verant for this one (even if it was an idea modified from AC and DAoC; it's still a great addition).<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, dear casters, that your skills are still needed, EVERYWHERE people can be bound except STARTING cities, and even then, if people want bound somewhere besides the rather remote location of the Soulbinde (the FP bank or west gate come to mind, 2 zones away from the soulbinder).  I don't think of this as a nerf to casters, but rather a welcome modification.<br>
<br>
Can we list locations of the soulbinders in Norrath, for the Bind Affinity challenged? They are supposed to be in each starting city of players (so no HHK  ). I know of two so far:<br>
<br>
Rivervale: At the inn by the water, standing on the deck<br>
Freeport: In south Freeport, at the in near the Priest of Discord, standing on the porch.<br>
<br>
Anyone else?<br>
<br>
<br>
Norik<br>
16th season paladin of Brell<br>
master smith, potter, baker, and fletcher  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ushayce.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shayce</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/01 11:30:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=934.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soulbinders!</span><hr size=1> <br>
